The Intervention Specialist 
 
The Intervention Specialist (IS) is our "integrity warrior" responsible for assessing exam sessions that have been escalated by Proctors in an Active Intervention. Upon escalation, the IS will evaluate the behavior of test-takers and determine whether or not the behavior is a violation of institutional policy. The IS will then either: validate and intervene with the test-taker, then mediate the session in accordance with institutional policy, or invalidate and de-escalate the session. This position will ensure academic integrity and execute prevention processes and best practices to mitigate loss due to breaches. 
 
The things youâ€™ll do: 
 
 Oversee proctoring sessions (guided by ProctorU checklist) ensuring that test-takers exhibiting suspicious behaviors are not violating institutional policies or exam rules 
 Professionally intervene in sessions where academic integrity concerns have been validated 
 Communicate effectively but professionally to take control of the session, remove the threat and gather evidence of the violation 
 Document academic integrity breaches and results of the intervention / investigation for distribution to instructor or test administrator 
 Follow all institutional and instructor standards and policies in regards to adjudication of the behavior and follow up actions 
 Adhere to quality control guidelines specific to ProctorU standards 
 Continuously learn and improve academic integrity prevention processes and best practices 
 
 
